<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<h:html xmlns:h="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:orx="http://openrosa.org/jr/xforms" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2002/xforms" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:jr="http://openrosa.org/javarosa" xmlns:vellum="http://commcarehq.org/xforms/vellum">
	<h:head>
		<h:title>Survey 2</h:title>
		<model>
			<instance>
				<data xmlns:jrm="http://dev.commcarehq.org/jr/xforms" xmlns="http://openrosa.org/formdesigner/5E654925-C1FA-4D1A-A172-E21BA89F01AC" uiVersion="1" version="1" name="Survey 2">
					<information />
					<sample_text_question />
					<sample_choice_question />
					<sample_number_question />
				</data>
			</instance>
			<bind nodeset="/data/information" />
			<bind nodeset="/data/sample_text_question" type="xsd:string" />
			<bind nodeset="/data/sample_choice_question" />
			<bind nodeset="/data/sample_number_question" type="xsd:int" />
			<itext>
				<translation lang="en" default="">
					<text id="information-label">
						<value>Add questions to this form:

* Use the toolbar at the top to add text, number, multiple choice, or other questions.
* For multiple or single choice questions, use the circle button in the toolbar to add more choices.
* For a given question, set the Question ID to the name of your data variable and the Label to the text you want the user to see.
* Add a hidden value to calculate (and not show) something in the form; for example, adding together two integer questions, or calculating age from a date of birth.

For more help, view our [Form Builder Overview](https://confluence.dimagi.com/display/commcarepublic/Form+Builder) or [Common Logic and Calculations Page](https://wiki.commcarehq.org/display/commcarepublic/Common+Logic+and+Calculations).

When you're ready to test your application, you can use the Try In CloudCare option on the main form page, or [install it on a phone using our deploy manager](https://confluence.dimagi.com/display/commcarepublic/Deploy+an+Application+on+CommCareHQ).</value>
						<value form="markdown">Add questions to this form:

* Use the toolbar at the top to add text, number, multiple choice, or other questions.
* For multiple or single choice questions, use the circle button in the toolbar to add more choices.
* For a given question, set the Question ID to the name of your data variable and the Label to the text you want the user to see.
* Add a hidden value to calculate (and not show) something in the form; for example, adding together two integer questions, or calculating age from a date of birth.

For more help, view our [Form Builder Overview](https://confluence.dimagi.com/display/commcarepublic/Form+Builder) or [Common Logic and Calculations Page](https://wiki.commcarehq.org/display/commcarepublic/Common+Logic+and+Calculations).

When you're ready to test your application, you can use the Try In CloudCare option on the main form page, or [install it on a phone using our deploy manager](https://confluence.dimagi.com/display/commcarepublic/Deploy+an+Application+on+CommCareHQ).</value>
					</text>
					<text id="sample_text_question-label">
						<value>Sample Text Question</value>
					</text>
					<text id="sample_choice_question-label">
						<value>Sample Choice Question</value>
					</text>
					<text id="sample_choice_question-choice1-label">
						<value>Choice 1</value>
					</text>
					<text id="sample_choice_question-choice2-label">
						<value>Choice 2</value>
					</text>
					<text id="sample_choice_question-choice3-label">
						<value>Choice 3</value>
					</text>
					<text id="sample_number_question-label">
						<value>Sample Number Question</value>
					</text>
				</translation>
			</itext>
		</model>
	</h:head>
	<h:body>
		<trigger ref="/data/information" appearance="minimal">
			<label ref="jr:itext('information-label')" />
		</trigger>
		<input ref="/data/sample_text_question">
			<label ref="jr:itext('sample_text_question-label')" />
		</input>
		<select1 ref="/data/sample_choice_question">
			<label ref="jr:itext('sample_choice_question-label')" />
			<item>
				<label ref="jr:itext('sample_choice_question-choice1-label')" />
				<value>choice1</value>
			</item>
			<item>
				<label ref="jr:itext('sample_choice_question-choice2-label')" />
				<value>choice2</value>
			</item>
			<item>
				<label ref="jr:itext('sample_choice_question-choice3-label')" />
				<value>choice3</value>
			</item>
		</select1>
		<input ref="/data/sample_number_question">
			<label ref="jr:itext('sample_number_question-label')" />
		</input>
	</h:body>
</h:html>
